				"id": "RLSA-2022:8400",
				"title": "Moderate: libtirpc security update",
				"description": "The libtirpc packages contain SunLib's implementation of transport-independent remote procedure call (TI-RPC) documentation, which includes a library required by programs in the nfs-utils and rpcbind packages.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libtirpc: DoS vulnerability with lots of connections (CVE-2021-46828)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nAdditional Changes:\n\nFor detailed information on changes in this release, see the Rocky Linux 9.1 Release Notes linked from the References section.",
